  <p>For maximum benefit, follow the <strong>listen → repeat → shadow</strong> method: First, listen to a short clip without reading. Then listen again while reading the transcript. Finally, play the audio and speak along simultaneously (shadowing). This trains both your ear and your mouth.</p>

  <h2 id="reading-resources">Reading Resources for Every Level</h2>
  <p>Reading is how you build vocabulary passively and reinforce grammar patterns. Start with material slightly below your level (you should understand 90%+ of the words) and gradually increase difficulty:</p>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
