  <h2 id="common-mistakes">Resource Mistakes Most Learners Make</h2>
  <p>Collecting apps is not the same as learning Chinese. Here are the most common mistakes learners make with study resources:</p>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
    <div style="background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fca5a5; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
      <strong style="color: #dc2626;">❌ Common Mistakes</strong>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <li>Downloading 10+ apps and using none consistently</li>
        <li>Only studying vocabulary without grammar or listening</li>
        <li>Avoiding speaking practice because it feels uncomfortable</li>
        <li>Spending more time choosing resources than using them</li>
        <li>Skipping review — learning new words but forgetting old ones</li>
        <li>Using only English-language explanations of Chinese</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div style="background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #86efac; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
      <strong style="color: #16a34a;">✅ Better Approach</strong>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <li>Pick 2–3 core tools and use them daily for 30 days</li>
        <li>Balance all four skills in every week of study</li>
        <li>Schedule regular speaking practice — even 5 minutes counts</li>
        <li>Commit to your tools for one month before switching</li>
        <li>Use Anki with spaced repetition to retain what you learn</li>
        <li>Gradually transition to Chinese-language learning resources</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>The best resource for learning Chinese is the one you actually use every day. Start with our <a href="/chinese/tools/">free Chinese learning tools</a> for pinyin, character practice, and vocabulary, then supplement with the apps and content listed above. Check out our <a href="/chinese/blog/pinyin-guide/">Complete Pinyin Guide</a> if you are just getting started, or explore <a href="/chinese/blog/hsk-preparation/">HSK Preparation Tips</a> if you are working toward a specific exam goal.</p>

